content.detailedDescription: I went out to my balcony, and looked up. i saw a silver disc just hovering, then a plane went right by this disc. the disc disappeared then re-appeared once the plane went by. the disc moved slightly to the south eas in a spinning motion, with a slight wobble. another plane came and the same thing happened. after the first plane a second disc was approaching from the north towards the original disc then dissappeared. then that disc after 15 minutes, came shooting across the sky just above the buildings in a north east direction. the first disc continued to move south east disappearing and re-appearing as planes went by. afterwards both just vanished from the sky. i felt a strange feeling as i watched the disc, almost as if it knew i was watching. i felt calm, even when the second disc shot across above the buildings. i did not think it was a ufo at first, but as i stared i could see the disc spinning as it hovered. it was a bright and clear day.
content.summary: There were two ufo's. one hovered and the second one was  scooting by.

content.detailedDescription: It was about 9:00pm and i was taking my trash out. it was a warm night which wasn't normal from where i am. i was looking at the stars which i normally do, and saw a weird object moving. the night sky was beautiful, not a cloud in sight, no cars driving by, no helicopters or air planes out. dead silent. i thought it was a helicopter but it was too quiet and too high up in the sky. there was no noise what so ever. no flashing lights, just a bright light. small as a star per-say. this thing or object was small like a star and bright. it was noticeable for me too see without my glasses on, and it moved slow, and was by its self. it kept a constant speed for quite some time. then while i was watching it, my eyes kind of shifted and i couldn't find it anymore. when i couldn't find it, i felt weird, not sure on what i saw in the night sky. i was outside for about 5 minuets or so, just feeling confused. i went inside my house and my sibling was wondering why i took so long.
content.summary: A moving star

content.detailedDescription: Traveling nw by car from st. paul we saw what we originally thought was a huge cluster of balloons. after watching for a couple minutes we realized they weren't balloons, or birds, or anything else we've seen before. they were reflectting light, then they would all disappear, only to show up again a few seconds later. we pulled over so i could try to get a couple pictures but only managed to get one.  these orbs would form various shapes (triangles at one point) then very quickly change to a different formation. we saw one plane fly directly below them. we followed them home and walked down the street to watch them until they were too far away to see anymore. black hawk in the area about an hour later.
content.summary: Large group of orbs

content.detailedDescription: I was walking home from the grocery store at approximately 7:05pm. it was still light out. i looked up and saw what i assumed was a stray mylar balloon at first, maybe 5 feet in diameter at a height a bit above the palm trees on my street. as i watched it, i noticed a bright greenish-blue light that seemed to radiate from the side of it. this made me keep watching. the object spun slowly and also wobbled but never tumbled in the sky. an orange light also flashed periodically. it floated over my head and then over the buildings on the other street and i watched it until it was out of view. i'm not 100% convinced that this was not a balloon because it looked weightless in the air and the metallic nature of a mylar balloon could explain the lights as merely reflections, but the constant spinning and the color of the lights make me wonder if it was something else.
content.summary: Metallic colored disc shaped object floated overhead. it was spinning and wobbling and had green and orange pulsating lights on the side.

content.detailedDescription: A friend was taking me home at around 10:45pm  when he said "do you see those two lights over there?"  he pointed towards the west, or our right, as we were heading south at the time.  i immediately saw the two lights and the light that was further south i could tell was an airplane as i could see it's blinking lights and could tell it was moving like many planes that fly over our town.  but the other light i knew was not normal.  it was much brighter and had a bluish white intensity to it.  we had stopped and was watching it and honestly at first i was not sure what we were looking at.  it did not move at all and i was beginning to think we were just seeing a bright star.  my friend turned the corner by now heading west and we got to a clear area so we could watch this light better. it continued to just sit in the same place but after about five minutes it made a very strange movement and moved in a short quick "s" pattern.  i said out loud, " did you just see it move?"  not sure that i had actually just seen that and my friend said that he did.  then it started moving up and down and at one point looked like it was making a circle.  it then moved towards the south for a short distance and then moved back to the north and stopped and just hovered again.  during this time it had changed it's light intensity and actually dimmed to a reddish colour and would get bright again.  it was doing this regularly now and then stared moving off towards the northwest.  it did not speed off it just headed off in no big hurry and we sat there and watched it as long as we could, to the point of where we could only really see it when it got bright before it turned red and then it just got too far and was out of our ability to see it anymore.
content.flightPath: Stationary,Hovering then path,Path with directional change
content.summary: Observed bright star like object that at first remained stationary then moved in a strange pattern

content.detailedDescription: Watching the kansas city royals baseball game on tv.  they did a closeup of the almost full moon.  i noticed something staring on the right side of the moon, (as viewed on my tv), that made a crossing pattern with different abrupt changes in direction.  the ufo went the full distance across the moon in a few, maybe 5 seconds.  i have it recorded, could not have been a satellite, plane or even birds due to its very strange quick movements. maybe others didn't notice it, because it was like a dot small.  my wife looked at it with me, and she agreed that it diffidently falls into the category of ufo! would be glad to share this recording, that was on national tv this evening! i imagine thousands seen it, but might not have been paying attention.  clearly there to see!
content.summary: Ufo crossing the moon on national tv

content.detailedDescription: I was driving and i felt something weird was about to happen to me in tellapathy . then it happened to me , my hand on the top of the skin , for one minute , i saw and felt a branding , it was red , the shape of a circle , within the red circle on my hand were letters , there were a lot of letters , i never seen any letters like these before , the letters were perfect on there edges and curves , the letters were like an alien language , they were so perfect . the letters   looked like advanced alien hyrogliphs writing . it hurt and for one minute the brand was there , and then the brand vanished off my skin on my hand , and the pain left .             a couple years went by . then in tellepathy , i knew something strange was about to happen to me . then it happened , this is what happened , my forehead felt like it opened and out of the opening were english numbers and english letters . the numbers were zeros and ones and the letters were a's and b's . the letters and numbers looked like a code , like this : 00000001111111 00000000aaaaaaaa 0000000000bbbbbbbbb 0000000000aaaaaaaa 00000000000111111111 000000000bbbbbbbb 00000000011111111 etc. , at a fast speed this code of numbers and letters were coming out of my forehead into thin air . thank you for reading what happened to me and i believe with no doubt extra terrestrials are observing me .
content.summary: I got branded on my hand of alien hiroglyph letters on my skin

content.detailedDescription: I was standing in the kitchen when i first witnessed what looked like an airplane descending from the air and i was afraid. i started to yell something. i think i was yelling something about the plane about to hit the trees. i thought it was going to hit my poplar trees. they are about 80 feet high. but before it hit it abruptly slowed down and maneuvered away from the trees with perfect agility. and then ascended back up into the sky. it was very quiet. the wind that day had been louder than the "plane" then about 20 minutes later i wanted to go out and see if there were anymore low flying planes. then not more than 1 or 2 minutes past and another plane quietly and slowly flew by me at like 25 mph and was about 15 feet off the ground i think i could have touched it if i were directly under it. and it made a strange sound like air being compressed and released.  then this one too flew back up over the trees and back into the sky .They both looked like a cigar shape. they had two wings on either side with what looked to be turbine type engines underneath, one on each side. i saw no windows. it was about 50 to 60 feet in length much larger than our average crop dusting plane and much quieter as well. they were both a dull grey with no writing anywhere. my first reaction was very upset i thought military guys were messing around my house. i called my husband home from work i was so upset. he told me it was impossible for them to be so quiet and move the way i was describing and i realized i may have seen a ufo. i have been looking on the internet for a similar "plane" and cannot find one. i hope you may be able to help me understand what i saw. thank you.
content.summary: About 2 in the afternoon i witnessed what initially looked like an air plane but flew very slow and quiet and very low to the ground. was also able to hover and change direction quickly. made almost no sound . it sound like air being compressed as it move

content.detailedDescription:
Time was about 1:20pm, april 22nd, 2016. st. louis park, mn. 5120 cedar lake road s., zip code 55413. i am on a short cigarette break during work. the day is bright, there aren't any clouds, and the sky is a nice blue color.

dave, my coworker, and i are smoking a cigarette back around by the shipping department doors where freight is received and picked up. we moved our chairs to sit in the sun, so we are farther away
from the building wall and out of its shadow. after smoking one cigarette we light another.

i don't remember what i was saying prior, but dave says "whoah, is that a bird?"

and i turn around. i put on my glasses but the sun is too bright, so i get up to get a closer look. he says maybe something like "it's just hovering/not moving."

i can't see it, but i see a plane fly pretty low and near. he points again and says, "look above the plane."

i run into the parking lot to get a closer look. i see the black dot. it is very high up. much higher than the airplane. it looks a little fuzzy - i cannot make out the shape really.

i looked at it for a total of 6 seconds, when it moved to the right (its left, my right). it moved fairly fast, faster than an airplane or helicopter. some trees obstructed my view
of seeing where it went, and i couldn't follow it. it seemed to have disappeared completely after that.

i saw two more airplanes in the area not more than 20 seconds after the object disappeared. 

my heart was pounding when i caught sight of it to the moment it left. i went inside immediately and wrote down everything i saw.
content.summary: I see a hovering black dot. it is very high up. much higher than a nearby airplane. i look for 6 seconds then it moves quickly to the east before disappearing out of sight.

content.detailedDescription:
I live fairly close to oc airport flight path.  we are used to seeing planes take off along with the noise.
this v-shaped craft had absolutely no noise!  it was a silouhette in the night sky with a uniform row of 4 lights down the bottom of each leg of the "v" and one light beneath the nose.  the lights flickered similar to looking into a fan with light behind it.
the night was extremely clear with beautiful stars and the light from a near full moon blocked by buildings but providing plenty of visibility,
i would guess that this craft was approx 1 mile off in the distance and no more than a few thousand feet off the ground.  it was heading in the direction of oc airport which is only 3-4 miles away for here.  consequently it would have had to change course very quickly after leaving my field of view.
the craft was definitely not on a landing flight pattern!
content.summary: Visual only-no sound!

content.detailedDescription:
I was standing in the middle of gennett rd. looking to ne, waiting for a ride. there was no traffic----it is a gravel rd. there was complete silence, and i saw 3 lights (or orbs) to the ne approx. 70 yds. from my driveway.
i first thought they were hunters looking for deer, so i walked quietly down the road to get a better view.  the lights then moved vertically very fast and also to the right & left, also up and down. i continued to watch  them until my ride came.  the lights seemed to be orbs, did not change in brightness at all. they disappeared at the time my ride came.
i was very intrigued.  i was not afraid at all.  the closest they were to me was approx. 60 ft.  when they disappeared, they just blinked out.
when i was viewing them, moving about playfully, very quickly.

someone i know saw something very similar about 2 weeks later, only the lights were directly above, also no sound, approximately same location.
i have not yet been able to reach that person about making a report.  

[some years ago (30 some years) i also observed lights in the sky in northern michigan, with my kids.  they were  similar to what i described in this report.]

i agreed to send in this report upon the urging of northern michigan fi judy kulka, whom i just recently met.

i do not have an e-mail address so am using judy kulka's.

content.detailedDescription:
I was at home in downingtown, pa around 6:30 pm on april 20, 2016, enjoying the weather and grilling dinner.  i was using my phone and trying to take a new profile picture for my facebook page. the next day upon reviewing one of images, i noticed two black shapes above my head in one of the six images, all taken within a minute or two. 

two shapes can be seen directly above my head when zooming all the way in. the shapes were both dark and similar in size and shape, either disc or cigar shaped, with a dome-like structure in the middle. one is at an angle and seems to show a reflection of the sun. i do not recall hearing, seeing or experiencing anything else unusual. 

this image struck me as odd. i am nowhere near qualified to analyze the shapes in the image in any capacity, but can rule out debris on the lens because none of the other images taken at the same time showed anything similar. they could be tiny insects perhaps, i had just returned from a run and would likely be an attractive snack for such a pest. 

i hope you enjoy the image and would let me know if you find it at all interesting!
content.summary: Reviewed an image and found 2 strange objects captured overhead.
